    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Species of bush native to China and cultivated in Japan for fiber, used for making paper. It is also known for bearing clusters of fragrant yellow flowers. The species was published twice in the same year, as E. papyrifera (Siebold &amp; Zucc.) and E. chrysantha, but in the absence of evidence supporting earlier publication, the name E. chrysantha more often has priority. </Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
